Anambra State governor, Prof Chukwuma Soludo, says wise counseling of Obi of Onitsha, Alfred Achebe, has helped the State and Ndigbo in tackling the issue of security. The governor spoke while celebrating the monarch on his 81st birthday and 20 years on the throne of Onitsha kingdom.   Njoku-led APGA begs pioneer chairman, Chekwas to return back     Abia teachers threaten indefinite strike over unpaid salary…     ‘Fake’ party returning officer lands in police…   In a statement Saturday in Awka, signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Chris Aburime, Soludo, said described Achebe as an outstanding personality in Nigeria. “On behalf of the government and People of Anambra State felicitates with the Obi of Onitsha, Igwe Nnaemeka Alfred Achebe, (Agbogidi) on his 81st birthday anniversary, today, (May 14 2022).”